1
00:00:08,550 --> 00:00:10,344
(ALL GROANING)

2
00:00:10,427 --> 00:00:11,929
Oh, my head!

3
00:00:12,054 --> 00:00:15,098
Time travel without a capsule,
that's a killer.

4
00:00:18,769 --> 00:00:20,854
Still, at least we made it.

5
00:00:20,938 --> 00:00:23,899
Earth, 21st century by the looks of it.

6
00:00:24,024 --> 00:00:27,653
-JACK: Talk about lucky.
-That wasn't luck. That was me.

7
00:00:29,112 --> 00:00:32,533
Hold it still!
Don't move, hold it still...

8
00:00:32,616 --> 00:00:35,452
I'm telling you, it's broken,
it hasn't worked for years...

9
00:00:35,577 --> 00:00:38,872
That's because you didn't have me!
Martha, grab hold.

10
00:00:38,956 --> 00:00:40,582
Now!

11
00:00:42,459 --> 00:00:44,962
The moral is, if you're gonna
get stuck at the end of the universe,

12
00:00:45,045 --> 00:00:47,756
get stuck with an ex-Time Agent
and his vortex manipulator.

13
00:00:47,839 --> 00:00:49,758
But this Master bloke,
he's got the Tardis.

14
00:00:49,841 --> 00:00:53,554
-He could be anywhere in time and space.
-No. He's here. Trust me.

15
00:00:53,637 --> 00:00:54,721
Who is he anyway?

16
00:00:54,805 --> 00:00:56,807
And that voice at the end,
that wasn't the Professor.

17
00:00:56,932 --> 00:00:59,226
If the Master's a Time Lord,
then he must've regenerated.

18
00:00:59,309 --> 00:01:02,145
-What does that mean?
-It means he's changed his face.

19
00:01:02,229 --> 00:01:05,107
Voice, body, everything, new man.

20
00:01:05,190 --> 00:01:07,859
(TAPPING)

21
00:01:08,068 --> 00:01:10,487
Then how are we gonna find him?

22
00:01:12,573 --> 00:01:15,659
I'll know him. The moment I see him.

23
00:01:15,784 --> 00:01:17,411
Time Lords always do.

24
00:01:17,494 --> 00:01:20,622
But hold on, if he could be anyone...

25
00:01:20,706 --> 00:01:25,419
We missed the election.
But it can't be...

26
00:01:25,502 --> 00:01:28,046
NEWSCASTER:
Mr Saxon has returned from the Palace,

27
00:01:28,171 --> 00:01:32,134
and is greeting the crowds
inside Saxon Headquarters.

28
00:01:32,968 --> 00:01:35,095
MARTHA: I said I knew that voice.

29
00:01:35,178 --> 00:01:36,680
When he spoke, inside the Tardis,

30
00:01:36,763 --> 00:01:40,017
I've heard that voice hundreds of times.
I've seen him, we all have.

31
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:42,728
That was the voice of Harold Saxon.

32
00:01:42,853 --> 00:01:45,564
That's him. He's Prime Minister.

33
00:01:47,649 --> 00:01:50,694
The Master is Prime Minister
of Great Britain.

34
00:01:52,946 --> 00:01:55,532
The Master and his wife?

35
00:01:55,657 --> 00:01:58,702
This country has been sick.

36
00:01:58,827 --> 00:02:00,662
This country needs healing.

37
00:02:00,746 --> 00:02:03,290
This country needs medicine.

38
00:02:03,415 --> 00:02:05,584
In fact, I'd go so far as to say,

39
00:02:05,709 --> 00:02:09,713
that what this country
really needs right now

40
00:02:09,796 --> 00:02:11,923
ls a Doctor.

41
00:02:14,593 --> 00:02:16,845
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

42
00:02:52,047 --> 00:02:54,466
-Finance report, sir.
-Military protocol, sir.

43
00:02:54,591 --> 00:02:56,426
-EC directive, sir.
-Annual budget, sir.

44
00:02:56,510 --> 00:02:58,387
Policy recommendations.

45
00:03:00,472 --> 00:03:02,391
I'm so proud of you, Harry.

46
00:03:05,602 --> 00:03:07,229
Bless.

47
00:03:07,896 --> 00:03:10,732
Sir, if you don't mind me asking.

48
00:03:10,816 --> 00:03:14,820
I'm sorry, but it's all a bit new,
what exactly do you want me to do?

49
00:03:14,945 --> 00:03:17,948
-Oh, yes, what was it...
-Tish, Letitia Jones.

50
00:03:18,031 --> 00:03:19,282
Tish.

51
00:03:19,366 --> 00:03:21,201
Well then, Tish.

52
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:26,123
You just stand there and look gorgeous.

53
00:03:29,084 --> 00:03:31,503
A glorious day. Downing Street rebuilt.

54
00:03:32,796 --> 00:03:34,840
The Cabinet in session.

55
00:03:36,133 --> 00:03:39,302
Let the work of government begin.

56
00:03:44,558 --> 00:03:48,979
Oh, go on, crack a smile.
It's funny, isn't it?

57
00:03:49,104 --> 00:03:52,733
Albert? Funny? No? Little bit?

58
00:03:52,816 --> 00:03:55,110
Very funny, sir.

59
00:03:55,193 --> 00:03:59,156
But if we could get down to business,
there is the matter of policy,

60
00:03:59,239 --> 00:04:01,658
-of which we have very little...
-No, no, no, no.

61
00:04:01,742 --> 00:04:05,078
Before we start all that,
I just want to say...

62
00:04:07,789 --> 00:04:11,084
Thank you. Thank you one and all.

63
00:04:11,168 --> 00:04:16,047
You ugly fat-faced
bunch of wet, snivelling traitors.

64
00:04:16,173 --> 00:04:19,301
Yes, quite, very funny, but I...

65
00:04:19,384 --> 00:04:22,804
No, no, that wasn't funny.

66
00:04:25,265 --> 00:04:27,434
You see, I'm not making
myself very clear,

67
00:04:27,517 --> 00:04:29,978
funny is like this...

68
00:04:31,980 --> 00:04:34,691
Not funny is like this...

69
00:04:34,816 --> 00:04:38,653
And right now, I'm not like...
I'm like...

70
00:04:39,905 --> 00:04:43,575
Because you are traitors. Yes, you are!

71
00:04:43,658 --> 00:04:46,661
As soon as you saw the vote
swinging my way,

72
00:04:46,745 --> 00:04:52,250
you abandoned your parties and you
jumped on the Saxon bandwagon. So...

73
00:04:54,669 --> 00:04:57,798
This is your reward.

74
00:05:00,717 --> 00:05:05,096
Excuse me, Prime Minister, do you
mind my asking, what is that?

75
00:05:05,222 --> 00:05:07,390
-(MUFFLED) A gas mask.
-I beg your pardon?

76
00:05:08,683 --> 00:05:10,644
It's a gas mask.

77
00:05:10,727 --> 00:05:14,773
Yes, but why are you wearing it?

78
00:05:14,898 --> 00:05:18,026
-(MUFFLED) Oh, because of the gas.
-I'm sorry?

79
00:05:18,109 --> 00:05:20,987
-Because of the gas.
-What gas?

80
00:05:22,030 --> 00:05:23,740
(MUFFLED) This gas.

81
00:05:36,753 --> 00:05:38,672
You're insane.

82
00:05:51,810 --> 00:05:52,853
Home!

83
00:05:52,936 --> 00:05:54,855
What you got?
Computer, laptop, anything.

84
00:05:54,938 --> 00:05:56,940
Who are you phoning?
You can't tell anyone we're here!

85
00:05:57,023 --> 00:05:58,441
Just some friends of mine
but there's no reply.

86
00:05:58,525 --> 00:05:59,901
Here you go. Any good?

87
00:05:59,985 --> 00:06:02,779
I'll show you the Saxon websites,
he's been around for ages.

88
00:06:02,946 --> 00:06:05,574
That's so weird,
"cause the day after the election,

89
00:06:05,657 --> 00:06:07,701
that's only four days after I met you.

90
00:06:07,784 --> 00:06:11,496
We went flying all round the universe
while he was here all the time.

91
00:06:11,580 --> 00:06:14,457
-You gonna tell us who he is?
-He's a Time Lord.

92
00:06:14,541 --> 00:06:17,335
What about the rest of it?
I mean, who'd call himself "the Master"?

93
00:06:17,419 --> 00:06:22,674
That's all you need to know.
Come on, show me Harold Saxon.

94
00:06:22,757 --> 00:06:24,718
TISH: Martha, where are you?
I've got this new job!

95
00:06:24,801 --> 00:06:27,387
You won't believe it it's weird.
They phoned me up out of the blue...

96
00:06:27,470 --> 00:06:29,222
Oh, like it matters!

97
00:06:29,306 --> 00:06:33,518
-I'm sorry, but you're not allowed in...
-"Harold Saxon, a modern Churchill.”

98
00:06:33,602 --> 00:06:36,187
It's the definitive think-piece
on the great man himself.

99
00:06:36,313 --> 00:06:37,981
Come on, sweetheart,
you must've read it!

100
00:06:38,064 --> 00:06:40,025
Um, not really. Sorry, I'm new.

101
00:06:40,108 --> 00:06:43,028
Mr Saxon does like a pretty face.
But I'm here to see Mrs Saxon.

102
00:06:43,153 --> 00:06:44,738
You can't just go barging in...

103
00:06:44,821 --> 00:06:48,491
Mrs Saxon, Vivien Rook, Sunday Mirror.
You've heard of me.

104
00:06:48,617 --> 00:06:51,202
Can't I just have an hour to myself?
It's been a hell of a day.

105
00:06:51,328 --> 00:06:53,330
Strike while the iron's hot,
that's what I say, Lucy...

106
00:06:53,496 --> 00:06:55,790
I can call you Lucy, can't I?

107
00:06:55,874 --> 00:06:58,877
Now, everyone's talking
about Harold Saxon,

108
00:06:58,960 --> 00:07:02,839
but I thought, what about the wife?
AW I need is 20 minutes.

109
00:07:02,923 --> 00:07:05,008
Oh, I think maybe we should wait...

110
00:07:05,091 --> 00:07:08,762
The headline's waiting to print,
"The Power Behind The Throne".

111
00:07:09,846 --> 00:07:11,681
-Really?
-Britain's First Lady.

112
00:07:11,765 --> 00:07:13,224
-Gosh.
-Front page.

113
00:07:13,350 --> 00:07:15,602
Oh! Well...

114
00:07:15,685 --> 00:07:18,730
I suppose... Oh, go on then, 20 minutes.

115
00:07:18,855 --> 00:07:20,106
Excellent!

116
00:07:20,190 --> 00:07:23,735
Thank you. Go, go...
What was it... Tish?

117
00:07:23,860 --> 00:07:26,696
Now you can leave us alone.

118
00:07:26,821 --> 00:07:31,159
-No, but I'm supposed to sit in.
-No, no. It's only a profile piece.

119
00:07:31,242 --> 00:07:37,332
You know, hair and clothes and nonsense.
There's a good girl, out you go.

120
00:07:37,457 --> 00:07:38,875
That's it.

121
00:07:40,210 --> 00:07:44,172
Mrs Saxon, I have reason to believe

122
00:07:45,382 --> 00:07:48,385
that you're in very great danger.
All of us, in fact.

123
00:07:48,468 --> 00:07:50,887
Not just the country,
but the whole world.

124
00:07:50,971 --> 00:07:52,764
No, I beg of you. Hear me out.

125
00:07:52,889 --> 00:07:57,560
-What are you talking about?
-Your husband is not who he says he is.

126
00:07:57,644 --> 00:08:01,898
I'm sorry, but it's a lie.
Everything's a lie.

127
00:08:02,732 --> 00:08:04,359
(MUSIC PLAYING)

128
00:08:06,069 --> 00:08:09,906
I'm voting Saxon.
He can tick my box any day!

129
00:08:10,031 --> 00:08:13,159
ALL: Vote Saxon! Go Harry!

130
00:08:13,576 --> 00:08:16,830
I think Mr Saxon is exactly what
this country needs.

131
00:08:16,913 --> 00:08:20,750
He's a very fine man.
And he's handsome, too.

132
00:08:22,085 --> 00:08:24,421
Former Minister of Defence,
first came to prominence

133
00:08:24,546 --> 00:08:27,007
when he shot down
the Racnoss on Christmas Eve.

134
00:08:27,090 --> 00:08:29,426
-Nice work by the way.
-Oh, thanks.

135
00:08:29,592 --> 00:08:33,805
But he goes back years, he's famous,
everyone knows the story. Look.

136
00:08:34,973 --> 00:08:39,352
Cambridge University, rugby Blue,
won the athletics thing, wrote a novel,

137
00:08:39,436 --> 00:08:41,813
went into business,
marriage, everything.

138
00:08:41,938 --> 00:08:44,733
He's got a whole life.

139
00:08:44,941 --> 00:08:47,527
All of it, the school days, his degree,

140
00:08:47,610 --> 00:08:50,447
even his mother and father,
it's all invented.

141
00:08:50,530 --> 00:08:53,783
Look, Harold Saxon
never went to Cambridge,

142
00:08:53,908 --> 00:08:56,077
there was no Harold Saxon!

143
00:08:56,161 --> 00:08:58,163
The thing is, it's obvious.

144
00:08:58,246 --> 00:09:01,833
The forgery is screaming out
and yet no one can see it!

145
00:09:01,916 --> 00:09:04,210
It's as if he's mesmerised
the entire world.

146
00:09:04,294 --> 00:09:05,837
I think perhaps you should leave now.

147
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:08,882
Eighteen months ago he became real.

148
00:09:08,965 --> 00:09:12,886
This is his first
honest-to-God appearance,

149
00:09:12,969 --> 00:09:16,222
just after the downfall
of Harriet Jones.

150
00:09:17,015 --> 00:09:22,645
And at the exact same time,
they launched the Archangel Network.

151
00:09:22,729 --> 00:09:24,564
Mrs Rook, now stop it!

152
00:09:24,647 --> 00:09:28,276
Even now, they've said that
the Cabinet's gone into seclusion.

153
00:09:28,359 --> 00:09:29,903
What does that mean, seclusion?

154
00:09:29,986 --> 00:09:34,157
-How should I know?
-But I've got plenty of research on you.

155
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:38,870
Yes, good family, Roedean,
not especially bright,

156
00:09:38,995 --> 00:09:43,124
but essentially harmless,
and that's why I'm asking you.

157
00:09:43,208 --> 00:09:46,127
Lucy, I am begging you,

158
00:09:46,211 --> 00:09:50,215
if you have seen anything,
heard anything,

159
00:09:50,340 --> 00:09:53,468
even the slightest thing that
would give you cause to doubt him...

160
00:09:53,551 --> 00:09:55,428
-I think...
-Yes?

161
00:09:56,846 --> 00:10:01,810
There was a time, when we first met,
I wondered...

162
00:10:01,893 --> 00:10:04,687
But he was so good
to my father, and he said...

163
00:10:04,854 --> 00:10:07,982
-What? Just tell me, sweetheart.
-The thing is...

164
00:10:10,819 --> 00:10:13,571
-I made my choice.
-I'm sorry?

165
00:10:14,447 --> 00:10:16,741
For better or for worse.

166
00:10:16,825 --> 00:10:19,035
Isn't that right, Harry?

167
00:10:20,537 --> 00:10:24,165
-My faithful companion.
-Mr Saxon.

168
00:10:25,375 --> 00:10:29,921
Prime Minister.
I was just having a little joke with...

169
00:10:30,046 --> 00:10:35,385
-Poor little Lucy, I didn't mean...
-Oh, but you're absolutely right.

170
00:10:37,137 --> 00:10:39,305
Harold Saxon doesn't exist.

171
00:10:41,349 --> 00:10:43,226
Then tell me...

172
00:10:44,561 --> 00:10:47,230
-who are you?
-I am the Master.

173
00:10:48,940 --> 00:10:51,484
And these are my friends.

174
00:10:57,407 --> 00:10:58,783
I'm sorry.

175
00:11:01,744 --> 00:11:04,539
Can't you hear it, Mrs Rook?

176
00:11:04,622 --> 00:11:07,959
-What do you mean?
-The drumbeat.

177
00:11:08,042 --> 00:11:11,963
The drums are coming closer and closer.

178
00:11:12,922 --> 00:11:15,341
SPHERE 1: 7he lady doesn't like us.

179
00:11:16,551 --> 00:11:19,053
-No...
-SPHERE 2: Silly lady.

180
00:11:19,137 --> 00:11:21,723
-No...
-SPHERE 2: Dead lady.

181
00:11:28,771 --> 00:11:30,190
(SCREAMING)

182
00:11:33,109 --> 00:11:34,819
(SCREAMING)

183
00:11:35,528 --> 00:11:37,614
But she knew!

184
00:11:37,739 --> 00:11:41,159
Harry, she knew everything.
You promised.

185
00:11:41,284 --> 00:11:43,578
You said Archangel
was one hundred per cent.

186
00:11:43,661 --> 00:11:45,496
Um. Ninety nine. Ninety eight?

187
00:11:45,580 --> 00:11:47,999
But if she's asking questions,
then who else?

188
00:11:48,082 --> 00:11:50,376
How much time have we got?

189
00:11:57,217 --> 00:12:00,178
Tomorrow morning, I promise.

190
00:12:02,388 --> 00:12:04,849
That's when everything ends.

191
00:12:06,809 --> 00:12:08,436
But he's got the Tardis.

192
00:12:08,519 --> 00:12:12,023
Maybe the Master went back in time,
and has been living here for decades.

193
00:12:12,148 --> 00:12:14,108
-No.
-Why not? Worked for me.

194
00:12:14,192 --> 00:12:15,693
When he was stealing the Tardis

195
00:12:15,777 --> 00:12:18,029
the only thing I could do
was fuse the coordinates.

196
00:12:18,112 --> 00:12:20,156
I locked them permanently.

197
00:12:22,450 --> 00:12:24,661
He can only travel between
the year one hundred trillion

198
00:12:24,744 --> 00:12:28,122
and the last place the Tardis landed.
Which is right here, right now.

199
00:12:28,206 --> 00:12:30,416
Yeah, but a little leeway?

200
00:12:30,500 --> 00:12:35,421
Well, 18 months, tops. The most
he could have been here is 18 months.

201
00:12:35,505 --> 00:12:37,882
So how's he managed all this?

202
00:12:38,007 --> 00:12:42,470
The Master was always sort of hypnotic,
but this is on a massive scale.

203
00:12:42,553 --> 00:12:44,222
-I was gonna vote for him.
-Really?

204
00:12:44,305 --> 00:12:48,059
Well, it was before I even met you.
And I liked him.

205
00:12:48,142 --> 00:12:51,020
-Me, too.
-Why do you say that?

206
00:12:52,188 --> 00:12:54,274
What was his policy,
what did he stand for?

207
00:12:54,357 --> 00:12:56,818
I don't know, he always sounded good.

208
00:12:57,986 --> 00:13:00,071
Like you could trust him.

209
00:13:01,239 --> 00:13:03,533
Just nice. He spoke about...

210
00:13:05,076 --> 00:13:07,954
I can't really remember,
but it was good.

211
00:13:09,330 --> 00:13:12,292
-Just the sound of his voice.
-What's that?

212
00:13:12,375 --> 00:13:14,252
-What?
-That! That tapping, that rhythm.

213
00:13:14,335 --> 00:13:17,255
-What are you doing?
-I don't know, it's nothing...

214
00:13:17,380 --> 00:13:19,590
I don't know!

215
00:13:22,427 --> 00:13:24,762
Our Lord and Master
is speaking to his kingdom.

216
00:13:24,846 --> 00:13:26,431
Britain, Britain, Britain.

217
00:13:27,056 --> 00:13:29,309
What extraordinary times we've had.

218
00:13:29,392 --> 00:13:32,854
Just a few years ago,
this world was so small.

219
00:13:32,937 --> 00:13:34,522
And then they came.

220
00:13:34,605 --> 00:13:37,400
Out of the unknown.
Falling from the skies.

221
00:13:37,525 --> 00:13:40,278
You've seen it happen.
Big Ben destroyed.

222
00:13:40,361 --> 00:13:42,155
A spaceship over London.

223
00:13:42,238 --> 00:13:48,202
All those ghosts and metal men,
the Christmas Star that came to kill.

224
00:13:48,286 --> 00:13:51,789
Time and time again and
the government told you nothing.

225
00:13:51,956 --> 00:13:54,751
Well not me. Not Harold Saxon.

226
00:13:54,834 --> 00:13:57,837
Because my purpose here today
is to tell you this.

227
00:13:57,920 --> 00:14:00,173
Citizens of Great Britain...

228
00:14:02,884 --> 00:14:04,427
I have been contacted.

229
00:14:04,552 --> 00:14:07,764
A message for humanity
from beyond the stars.

230
00:14:09,724 --> 00:14:11,351
SPHERE: People of the Earth.

231
00:14:11,434 --> 00:14:15,104
We come in peace.
We bring you great gifts.

232
00:14:15,188 --> 00:14:18,483
We bring technology and
wisdom and protection.

233
00:14:18,608 --> 00:14:21,611
And all we ask in return
Is your friendship.

234
00:14:22,111 --> 00:14:23,946
Oh, sweet.

235
00:14:24,655 --> 00:14:27,241
And this species has identified itself.

236
00:14:27,325 --> 00:14:30,119
-They're called the Toclafane.
-What?

237
00:14:30,203 --> 00:14:32,372
And tomorrow morning they will appear,

238
00:14:32,455 --> 00:14:35,750
not in secret, but to all of you.

239
00:14:35,833 --> 00:14:39,545
Diplomatic relations
with a new species will begin.

240
00:14:39,629 --> 00:14:45,093
Tomorrow, we take our place
in the universe.

241
00:14:45,301 --> 00:14:48,012
Every man, woman and child,

242
00:14:48,096 --> 00:14:51,641
every teacher and chemist
and lorry driver

243
00:14:51,766 --> 00:14:55,269
and farmer and,
oh, I don't know, every...

244
00:14:55,353 --> 00:14:57,021
medical student?

245
00:15:00,817 --> 00:15:02,568
DOCTOR: Out!

246
00:15:02,652 --> 00:15:04,487
(BEEPING)

247
00:15:16,416 --> 00:15:18,835
-All right? Martha?
-Fine, yeah, I'm fine.

248
00:15:18,918 --> 00:15:20,420
-What are you doing?
-He knows about me,

249
00:15:20,503 --> 00:15:22,797
-what about my family?
-Don't tell them anything.

250
00:15:22,880 --> 00:15:25,174
I'll do what I like!

251
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:29,679
-Mum! Oh, my God, you're there.
-Course I'm here, sweetheart.

252
00:15:29,762 --> 00:15:32,473
-You all right?
-I'm fine, no, I'm fine.

253
00:15:32,557 --> 00:15:35,017
Mum, has there been anyone
asking about me?

254
00:15:35,101 --> 00:15:37,728
Martha, I think perhaps
you should come round.

255
00:15:37,812 --> 00:15:40,273
-I can't, not now.
-No, but it's your father.

256
00:15:40,356 --> 00:15:43,234
We've been talking, and we thought
we might give it another go.

257
00:15:43,359 --> 00:15:46,362
-Don't be so daft! Since when?
-Just come round.

258
00:15:46,654 --> 00:15:48,823
Come to the house. We can celebrate.

259
00:15:48,906 --> 00:15:51,117
You'd never get back with him
in a million years.

260
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:53,244
Ask him yourself.

261
00:15:56,289 --> 00:15:59,375
-Martha, it's me.
-Dad? What are you doing there?

262
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:02,044
Like your mother said.
Come round, we can explain everything.

263
00:16:02,128 --> 00:16:04,964
Dad, just say yes or no.

264
00:16:05,089 --> 00:16:07,383
Is there someone else there?

265
00:16:09,218 --> 00:16:13,264
-Yes. Just run! Listen to me, just run!
-Clive, stop it!

266
00:16:13,389 --> 00:16:15,308
-I don't know who they are!
-You stupid man!

267
00:16:15,391 --> 00:16:17,977
-We're trying to help her!
-Dad, what's going?

268
00:16:19,645 --> 00:16:22,899
-We've got to get Martha away from him!
-I've gotta help them.

269
00:16:23,024 --> 00:16:24,775
That's exactly what they want,
it's a trap!

270
00:16:24,901 --> 00:16:26,486
I don't care!

271
00:16:29,113 --> 00:16:30,907
Get off!

272
00:16:32,450 --> 00:16:35,244
It is your fault! All of you!

273
00:16:35,369 --> 00:16:37,788
You voted Saxon! You did this!

274
00:16:41,584 --> 00:16:43,002
Corner!

275
00:16:45,505 --> 00:16:50,426
Mr Saxon, we have Condition Red on
the Jones Plan, we're taking them in.

276
00:16:51,010 --> 00:16:53,721
-All of them.
-But I was helping you!

277
00:16:53,930 --> 00:16:55,932
(PHONE RINGING)

278
00:16:56,015 --> 00:16:58,351
Come on, Tish, pick up.

279
00:16:58,434 --> 00:17:00,436
(RINGING)

280
00:17:00,561 --> 00:17:03,981
Martha, can't talk now! We've just made
First Contact, did you see?

281
00:17:04,106 --> 00:17:06,025
What are you doing! Get off!

282
00:17:06,108 --> 00:17:08,778
-Linda, tell them!
-What's happening? Tish?

283
00:17:08,861 --> 00:17:10,780
It's your fault! It's all your fault!

284
00:17:10,905 --> 00:17:13,783
I was helping you! Get off me!

285
00:17:16,786 --> 00:17:20,039
Martha! Get out of here, get out!

286
00:17:20,122 --> 00:17:21,832
Target identified!

287
00:17:21,958 --> 00:17:23,251
Martha, reverse!

288
00:17:23,334 --> 00:17:25,461
-Take aim!
-Get out now!

289
00:17:25,962 --> 00:17:27,213
Fire!

290
00:17:27,880 --> 00:17:29,549
Move it!

291
00:17:34,136 --> 00:17:36,013
Take them away!

292
00:17:41,477 --> 00:17:43,479
The only place he can go
was planet Earth!

293
00:17:43,604 --> 00:17:44,855
Careful!

294
00:17:44,939 --> 00:17:46,732
Martha, listen to me, do as I say.

295
00:17:46,816 --> 00:17:50,987
We gotta ditch this car.
Pull over. Right now!

296
00:17:58,244 --> 00:18:00,997
-Martha, come on.
-Leo!

297
00:18:01,080 --> 00:18:03,708
Oh, thank God, Leo, you've gotta listen
to me. Where are you?

298
00:18:03,791 --> 00:18:06,419
I'm in Brighton.
Yeah, we came down with Boxer.

299
00:18:06,502 --> 00:18:08,212
Did you see that Saxon thing on telly?

300
00:18:08,337 --> 00:18:10,339
Leo, just listen to me, don't go home.

301
00:18:10,464 --> 00:18:15,344
I'm telling you, don't phone Mum or Dad
or Tish, you've gotta hide.

302
00:18:15,428 --> 00:18:18,306
-Shut up.
-On my life, you've gotta trust me.

303
00:18:18,389 --> 00:18:22,018
Go to Boxer's, stay with him,
don't tell anyone, just hide.

304
00:18:22,143 --> 00:18:25,855
Ooh, nice little game
of hide and seek, I love that!

305
00:18:25,938 --> 00:18:28,774
But I'll find you, Martha Jones.

306
00:18:28,858 --> 00:18:31,319
Been a long time since
we saw each other.

307
00:18:31,402 --> 00:18:34,113
Must be, what, a hundred trillion years?

308
00:18:34,196 --> 00:18:36,616
Let them go, Saxon!

309
00:18:36,699 --> 00:18:38,576
Do you hear me? Let them go!

310
00:18:41,037 --> 00:18:43,039
I'm here.

311
00:18:54,467 --> 00:18:56,594
-Doctor.
-Master.

312
00:18:57,720 --> 00:18:59,096
(SIGHS)

313
00:18:59,180 --> 00:19:01,098
I like it when you use my name.

314
00:19:01,223 --> 00:19:04,143
You chose it. Psychiatrist's field day.

315
00:19:04,644 --> 00:19:08,731
As you chose yours.
The man who makes people better.

316
00:19:09,273 --> 00:19:11,692
How sanctimonious is that?

317
00:19:11,901 --> 00:19:15,029
So, Prime Minister, then?

318
00:19:15,112 --> 00:19:17,657
I know! It's good, isn't it?

319
00:19:17,740 --> 00:19:21,243
Who are those creatures?
There's no such thing as the Toclafane.

320
00:19:21,327 --> 00:19:23,371
That's just a made-up name,
like the bogeyman.

321
00:19:23,454 --> 00:19:28,417
Do you remember all those fairy tales
about the Toclafane when we were kids?

322
00:19:28,501 --> 00:19:30,544
Back home?

323
00:19:30,670 --> 00:19:32,505
Where is it, Doctor?

324
00:19:34,382 --> 00:19:37,134
-Gone.
-How can Gallifrey be gone?

325
00:19:40,388 --> 00:19:42,098
It burnt.

326
00:19:43,432 --> 00:19:45,559
And the Time Lords?

327
00:19:46,811 --> 00:19:48,187
Dead.

328
00:19:49,271 --> 00:19:51,774
And the Daleks. More or less.

329
00:19:52,983 --> 00:19:54,402
What happened to you?

330
00:19:54,485 --> 00:19:56,445
The Time Lords only resurrected me

331
00:19:56,570 --> 00:20:00,199
because they knew I'd be
the perfect warrior for a Time War.

332
00:20:00,324 --> 00:20:04,578
I was there when the Dalek Emperor
took control of the Cruciform.

333
00:20:05,413 --> 00:20:07,039
I saw it.

334
00:20:07,748 --> 00:20:09,375
I ran.

335
00:20:10,668 --> 00:20:12,628
I ran so far.

336
00:20:14,046 --> 00:20:17,633
Made myself human
so they would never find me,

337
00:20:19,135 --> 00:20:20,469
because...

338
00:20:22,471 --> 00:20:24,140
I was so scared.

339
00:20:25,391 --> 00:20:26,809
I know.

340
00:20:27,309 --> 00:20:30,521
All of them? But not you.

341
00:20:30,604 --> 00:20:32,565
Which must mean...

342
00:20:32,648 --> 00:20:35,443
I was the only one who could end it.

343
00:20:37,695 --> 00:20:39,655
And I tried, I did, I tried everything.

344
00:20:39,780 --> 00:20:42,491
What did it feel like, though?

345
00:20:43,325 --> 00:20:47,163
Two almighty civilisations burning.

346
00:20:48,414 --> 00:20:50,458
Oh, tell me, how did that feel?

347
00:20:50,541 --> 00:20:54,378
-Stop it.
-You must have been like God.

348
00:20:55,546 --> 00:20:58,591
I've been alone ever since.

349
00:20:58,674 --> 00:21:02,344
But not any more. Don't you see,
all we've got is each other?

350
00:21:02,511 --> 00:21:04,138
Are you asking me out on a date?

351
00:21:04,221 --> 00:21:06,432
You could stop this right now,
we could leave this planet.

352
00:21:06,515 --> 00:21:09,101
We can fight across the constellations
if that's what you want.

353
00:21:09,185 --> 00:21:11,270
But not on Earth.

354
00:21:12,188 --> 00:21:14,023
Too late.

355
00:21:15,566 --> 00:21:18,444
-Why do you say that?
-The drumming.

356
00:21:19,862 --> 00:21:21,947
Can't you hear it?

357
00:21:22,031 --> 00:21:24,533
I thought it would stop,
but it never does.

358
00:21:24,658 --> 00:21:28,037
It never, ever stops. Inside my head.

359
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:32,082
The drumming, Doctor,
the constant drumming.

360
00:21:32,750 --> 00:21:34,919
I can help you. Please let me help.

361
00:21:35,002 --> 00:21:38,714
It's everywhere. Listen, listen, listen.

362
00:21:39,799 --> 00:21:41,759
(TAPPING)

363
00:21:42,885 --> 00:21:44,887
Here come the drums.

364
00:21:45,429 --> 00:21:48,474
Here come the drums.

365
00:21:52,186 --> 00:21:54,271
What have you done?

366
00:21:54,563 --> 00:21:58,025
Tell me how you've done this.
What are those creatures? Tell me!

367
00:21:58,108 --> 00:21:59,610
Ooh, look, you're on TV!

368
00:21:59,735 --> 00:22:03,072
-Stop it. Answer me.
-No, really, you're on telly!

369
00:22:03,948 --> 00:22:06,283
You and your little band.

370
00:22:06,408 --> 00:22:09,578
Which, by the way, is ticking
every demographic box.

371
00:22:09,662 --> 00:22:12,915
So congratulations on that.
Look, there you are!

372
00:22:13,791 --> 00:22:17,419
NEWSCASTER: They are known to be armed
and extremely dangerous.

373
00:22:17,503 --> 00:22:21,715
You're public enemies
number one, two and three!

374
00:22:21,799 --> 00:22:24,844
Oh, and you can tell handsome Jack

375
00:22:24,927 --> 00:22:29,515
that I've sent his little gang off on
a wild goose chase to the Himalayas

376
00:22:29,598 --> 00:22:32,101
so he won't be getting
any help from them.

377
00:22:33,060 --> 00:22:37,481
Now go on, off you go.
Why not start by turning to the...right?

378
00:22:39,608 --> 00:22:41,235
He can see us.

379
00:22:41,318 --> 00:22:43,821
Ooh, you public menace.

380
00:22:43,946 --> 00:22:46,949
Better start running! Go on, run!

381
00:22:50,035 --> 00:22:51,829
He's got control of everything.

382
00:22:51,954 --> 00:22:56,166
-What do we do?
-We've got nowhere to go.

383
00:22:56,250 --> 00:23:00,588
-Doctor, what do we do?
-Run, Doctor!

384
00:23:01,463 --> 00:23:04,550
-Run for your life!
-We run.

385
00:23:09,430 --> 00:23:11,432
I said, run!

386
00:23:14,894 --> 00:23:18,814
Tomorrow morning, Britain will be
welcoming an extraterrestrial species...

387
00:23:19,231 --> 00:23:20,983
The President is said to be furious that

388
00:23:21,108 --> 00:23:23,193
Great Britain's
taken unilateral action...

389
00:23:23,819 --> 00:23:25,738
(SPEAKING MANDARIN)

390
00:23:42,796 --> 00:23:44,798
Have you seen these things?

391
00:23:45,925 --> 00:23:48,427
This planet's amazing.

392
00:23:48,844 --> 00:23:54,308
Television in their stomach.
Now that is evolution!

393
00:23:55,142 --> 00:23:58,604
-Is the machine ready?
-Tomorrow morning.

394
00:23:59,688 --> 00:24:03,776
It reaches critical at 8:02 precisely.

395
00:24:03,901 --> 00:24:07,780
We have to escape
because it's coming, sir, the darkness.

396
00:24:07,863 --> 00:24:12,117
The never-ending darkness,
and the terrible, terrible cold.

397
00:24:12,201 --> 00:24:14,536
We have to run and run and run.

398
00:24:14,620 --> 00:24:17,206
8:00, tomorrow morning.

399
00:24:19,083 --> 00:24:23,212
Tell your people the world is waiting.

400
00:24:38,811 --> 00:24:40,646
JACK: How was it?

401
00:24:40,729 --> 00:24:42,815
I don't think anyone saw me.
Anything new?

402
00:24:42,898 --> 00:24:44,817
I got this tuned into
the government wavelength

403
00:24:44,900 --> 00:24:48,153
-so we can follow what Saxon's doing.
-I meant about my family.

404
00:24:48,237 --> 00:24:51,657
Still says the Jones family
taken in for questioning.

405
00:24:51,740 --> 00:24:54,118
Tell you what, though,
no mention of Leo.

406
00:24:54,243 --> 00:24:56,537
He's not as daft as he looks.

407
00:24:57,454 --> 00:25:00,165
I'm talking about my brother,
on the run, how did this happen?

408
00:25:00,249 --> 00:25:03,752
-Nice chips.
-Actually, they're not bad.

409
00:25:09,425 --> 00:25:12,511
So, Doctor, who is he?

410
00:25:12,594 --> 00:25:16,348
How come the ancient society of
Time Lords created a psychopath?

411
00:25:16,515 --> 00:25:17,850
And what is he to you?

412
00:25:17,933 --> 00:25:20,561
-Like a colleague, or...
-A friend at first.

413
00:25:20,644 --> 00:25:24,940
Thought you were gonna say he was
your secret brother or something.

414
00:25:25,024 --> 00:25:27,860
You've been watching too much TV.

415
00:25:27,943 --> 00:25:30,821
But all the legends of Gallifrey
made it sound so perfect.

416
00:25:30,946 --> 00:25:35,576
Well, perfect to look at, maybe.
And it was, it was beautiful.

417
00:25:37,077 --> 00:25:40,622
They used to call it
the Shining World of the Seven Systems.

418
00:25:41,623 --> 00:25:44,376
And on the continent of Wild Endeavour,

419
00:25:45,461 --> 00:25:48,630
in the mountains of Solace and Solitude,

420
00:25:48,756 --> 00:25:51,633
there stood the Citadel
of the Time Lords.

421
00:25:54,928 --> 00:25:58,182
The oldest and most mighty
race in the universe,

422
00:26:00,184 --> 00:26:03,103
looking down on the galaxies below,

423
00:26:03,979 --> 00:26:05,731
sworn never to interfere.

424
00:26:06,607 --> 00:26:08,150
Only to watch.

425
00:26:08,942 --> 00:26:10,903
Children of Gallifrey,

426
00:26:11,028 --> 00:26:13,822
taken from their families
at the age of eight

427
00:26:13,947 --> 00:26:15,741
to enter the Academy.

428
00:26:15,866 --> 00:26:18,744
And some say that's where it all began.

429
00:26:19,787 --> 00:26:21,622
When he was a child.

430
00:26:23,665 --> 00:26:26,335
That's when the Master saw eternity.

431
00:26:29,546 --> 00:26:31,590
As a novice,
he was taken for initiation.

432
00:26:31,673 --> 00:26:35,094
He stood in front of
the Untempered Schism,

433
00:26:35,177 --> 00:26:38,013
it's a gap in the fabric of reality

434
00:26:38,097 --> 00:26:40,933
through which could be seen
the whole of the Vortex.

435
00:26:41,016 --> 00:26:42,684
You stand there,

436
00:26:44,186 --> 00:26:45,854
eight years old,

437
00:26:48,023 --> 00:26:51,777
staring at the raw power of
time and space. Just a child.

438
00:26:55,114 --> 00:26:57,116
Some would be inspired.

439
00:26:58,659 --> 00:27:00,536
Some would run away.

440
00:27:03,705 --> 00:27:05,958
And some would go mad.

441
00:27:14,967 --> 00:27:18,345
-I don't know.
-MARTHA: What about you?

442
00:27:18,428 --> 00:27:22,099
Oh, the ones that ran away.
I never stopped.

443
00:27:22,182 --> 00:27:23,892
(BEEPING)

444
00:27:26,061 --> 00:27:28,438
Encrypted channel with files attached.

445
00:27:28,522 --> 00:27:31,567
-Don't recognise it.
-Hmm, patch it through to the laptop.

446
00:27:31,692 --> 00:27:35,612
Since we're telling stories,
there's something I haven't told you.

447
00:27:40,325 --> 00:27:41,994
You work for Torchwood?

448
00:27:42,077 --> 00:27:44,246
I swear to you, it's different,
it's changed.

449
00:27:44,329 --> 00:27:45,831
There's only half a dozen of us now.

450
00:27:45,914 --> 00:27:47,666
Everything Torchwood did
and you're part of it?

451
00:27:47,749 --> 00:27:49,918
The old regime was destroyed
at Canary Wharf.

452
00:27:50,043 --> 00:27:53,463
I rebuilt it, I changed it,
and when I did that, I did it for you.

453
00:27:53,589 --> 00:27:55,757
In your honour.

454
00:28:04,141 --> 00:28:07,311
If I haven't returned to my desk by 2200

455
00:28:07,436 --> 00:28:09,980
this file will be emailed to Torchwood.

456
00:28:10,063 --> 00:28:13,358
Which means if you're watching this,
then I'm...

457
00:28:14,151 --> 00:28:17,154
Anyway, the Saxon files are attached,

458
00:28:17,279 --> 00:28:20,115
but take a look
at the Archangel document.

459
00:28:20,199 --> 00:28:23,368
That's when it all started,
when Harry Saxon became Minister

460
00:28:23,452 --> 00:28:26,538
in charge of launching
the Archangel Network.

461
00:28:26,622 --> 00:28:29,958
-DOCTOR: What's the Archangel Network?
-I've got Archangel, everyone's got it.

462
00:28:30,042 --> 00:28:32,753
It's the mobile phone network.
'Cause look, it's gone worldwide.

463
00:28:32,836 --> 00:28:34,713
They've got 15 satellites in orbit.

464
00:28:34,796 --> 00:28:38,508
Even the other networks,
they're all carried by Archangel.

465
00:28:38,592 --> 00:28:41,762
It's in the phones!
Oh, I said he was a hypnotist.

466
00:28:41,845 --> 00:28:44,806
Wait, wait, wait. Hold on.

467
00:28:44,890 --> 00:28:46,975
(BEEPING)

468
00:28:47,100 --> 00:28:50,604
There it is! That rhythm.
It's everywhere.

469
00:28:50,687 --> 00:28:53,357
Ticking away in the subconscious.

470
00:28:53,440 --> 00:28:56,735
-What is it, mind control?
-No, no, no, no. Subtler than that.

471
00:28:56,818 --> 00:28:58,612
Any strong-willed people
would question it.

472
00:28:58,695 --> 00:29:00,739
But contained in that rhythm,
in layers of code,

473
00:29:00,822 --> 00:29:04,368
"Vote Saxon. Believe in me."
Whispering to the world.

474
00:29:05,202 --> 00:29:07,579
Oh! Yes!
That's how he hid himself from me!

475
00:29:07,663 --> 00:29:09,915
'Cause I should've sensed
there was another Time Lord on Earth.

476
00:29:09,998 --> 00:29:12,668
I should've known way back,
but the signal cancelled him out.

477
00:29:12,751 --> 00:29:14,336
Any way you can stop it?

478
00:29:14,419 --> 00:29:16,880
Not from down here.
But now we know how he's doing it.

479
00:29:16,964 --> 00:29:19,341
-And we can fight back?
-Oh, yes!

480
00:29:39,069 --> 00:29:41,363
Three Tardis keys,
three pieces of the Tardis,

481
00:29:41,446 --> 00:29:42,906
all with low-level perception properties

482
00:29:42,990 --> 00:29:45,200
because the Tardis
is designed to blend in.

483
00:29:45,284 --> 00:29:46,451
Well, sort of, but now,

484
00:29:46,535 --> 00:29:48,996
the Archangel Network's got
a second low-level signal.

485
00:29:49,079 --> 00:29:52,374
Weld the key to the network,
and Martha...

486
00:29:52,499 --> 00:29:53,959
Look at me, you can see me, yes?

487
00:29:54,042 --> 00:29:56,169
-Yep!
-What about now?

488
00:30:04,803 --> 00:30:06,805
No, I'm here, look at me.

489
00:30:06,888 --> 00:30:11,059
It's like I know you're there,
but I don't want to know.

490
00:30:11,184 --> 00:30:12,477
And back again!

491
00:30:12,561 --> 00:30:15,230
See? It just shifts your perception,
a tiny little bit.

492
00:30:15,397 --> 00:30:18,358
Doesn't make us invisible.
Just unnoticed.

493
00:30:18,442 --> 00:30:20,610
Oh! I know what it's like! It's like...

494
00:30:20,694 --> 00:30:23,405
It's like when you fancy someone,
and they don't even know you exist.

495
00:30:23,572 --> 00:30:25,907
That's what it's like. Come on!

496
00:30:28,410 --> 00:30:30,370
You too, huh?

497
00:30:34,458 --> 00:30:35,959
DOCTOR: Don't run.

498
00:30:37,044 --> 00:30:39,880
Don't shout, just keep your voice down.

499
00:30:40,630 --> 00:30:43,300
Draw attention to yourself
and the spell is broken.

500
00:30:43,383 --> 00:30:45,510
Just keep to the shadows.

501
00:30:45,594 --> 00:30:46,887
-Like ghosts.
-Yeah.

502
00:30:46,970 --> 00:30:50,098
That's what we are. Ghosts.

503
00:31:11,119 --> 00:31:14,664
And as the eyes of the world
turn towards Great Britain

504
00:31:14,790 --> 00:31:19,419
sources indicate that Air Force One
has landed on British soil tonight.

505
00:31:30,138 --> 00:31:31,890
Mr President, sir!

506
00:31:32,849 --> 00:31:35,477
Mr Saxon, the British Army
will stand down.

507
00:31:35,602 --> 00:31:38,313
From now on, UNIT has control
of this operation.

508
00:31:38,397 --> 00:31:40,607
You make it sound like an invasion.

509
00:31:40,690 --> 00:31:44,403
The First Contact Policy was decided by
the Security Council in 1968

510
00:31:44,486 --> 00:31:45,904
and you've just gone and ignored it.

511
00:31:45,987 --> 00:31:49,116
Well, you know what it's like,
new job, all that paperwork.

512
00:31:49,199 --> 00:31:50,909
I think it's down
the back of the settee.

513
00:31:50,992 --> 00:31:53,870
I did have a quick look,
I found a pen, a sweet,

514
00:31:53,995 --> 00:31:57,374
a bus ticket, and...
Have you met the wife?

515
00:31:58,917 --> 00:32:01,002
Mr Saxon,
I'm not sure what your game is,

516
00:32:01,086 --> 00:32:02,671
but there are provisions at the UN

517
00:32:02,754 --> 00:32:06,508
to have you removed from office
unless you are very, very careful.

518
00:32:06,633 --> 00:32:08,385
Is that understood?

519
00:32:10,178 --> 00:32:14,516
Are you taking this seriously?
To business.

520
00:32:14,599 --> 00:32:18,478
We've accessed your files
on these Toclafane.

521
00:32:18,562 --> 00:32:21,690
But First Contact cannot take
place on any sovereign soil.

522
00:32:21,773 --> 00:32:25,193
To that purpose, the aircraft carrier
Valiant is en route.

523
00:32:25,277 --> 00:32:27,946
The rendezvous
will take place there at 8:00 am.

524
00:32:28,029 --> 00:32:29,948
(MUMBLING)

525
00:32:30,031 --> 00:32:32,451
You're trying my patience, sir.

526
00:32:35,036 --> 00:32:39,749
-So America is completely in charge?
-Since Britain elected an ass, yes.

527
00:32:39,833 --> 00:32:41,293
I'll see you on board the Valiant.

528
00:32:41,376 --> 00:32:45,046
It still will be televised, though,
won't it?

529
00:32:45,130 --> 00:32:48,592
Because I promised,
and the whole world is watching.

530
00:32:48,675 --> 00:32:52,971
Since it's too late to pull out,
the world will be watching.

531
00:32:53,054 --> 00:32:54,723
Me.

532
00:32:59,519 --> 00:33:01,855
The last President of America.

533
00:33:04,983 --> 00:33:08,111
We have a private plane
ready and waiting.

534
00:33:08,195 --> 00:33:11,490
We should reach the Valiant
within the hour.

535
00:33:11,573 --> 00:33:13,074
My darling...

536
00:33:36,640 --> 00:33:38,350
(SIREN WAILING)

537
00:33:44,773 --> 00:33:46,274
(LAUGHING)

538
00:33:46,358 --> 00:33:48,026
Hi, guys!

539
00:33:48,109 --> 00:33:50,529
What are you doing!

540
00:33:50,612 --> 00:33:53,823
-All! All will be revealed.
-Saxon!

541
00:33:53,907 --> 00:33:55,200
Oh, my God!

542
00:33:55,325 --> 00:33:56,826
-Don't move.
-But...

543
00:33:56,952 --> 00:33:58,995
Don't!

544
00:33:59,162 --> 00:34:01,289
I'm gonna kill him.

545
00:34:01,373 --> 00:34:03,333
What say I use this perception filter

546
00:34:03,416 --> 00:34:06,294
to walk up behind him
and break his neck?

547
00:34:06,836 --> 00:34:09,214
Now that sounds like Torchwood.

548
00:34:10,048 --> 00:34:11,800
Still a good plan.

549
00:34:12,467 --> 00:34:16,805
He's a Time Lord.
Which makes him my responsibility.

550
00:34:17,639 --> 00:34:21,810
I'm not here to kill him.
I'm here to save him.

551
00:34:23,979 --> 00:34:27,482
Aircraft carrier Valiant
that's a UNIT ship,

552
00:34:27,607 --> 00:34:32,153
at 58.2 North, 10.02 East.

553
00:34:32,237 --> 00:34:34,239
How do we get on board?

554
00:34:34,322 --> 00:34:37,951
-Does that thing work as a teleport?
-Since you revamped it, yeah.

555
00:34:38,034 --> 00:34:39,703
Coordinates set.

556
00:34:47,210 --> 00:34:50,547
-MARTHA: Oh, that thing is rough!
-I've had worse nights.

557
00:34:50,630 --> 00:34:51,881
(SCREAMS)

558
00:34:53,049 --> 00:34:56,678
-Welcome to the Valiant.
-It's dawn.

559
00:34:58,513 --> 00:35:01,224
Hold on, I thought this was a ship,
where's the sea?

560
00:35:01,349 --> 00:35:03,977
A ship for the 21st century.

561
00:35:04,436 --> 00:35:07,063
Protecting the skies of planet Earth.

562
00:35:19,242 --> 00:35:21,119
OVER PA: Europe now online.

563
00:35:21,202 --> 00:35:25,373
Awaiting confirmation from South America
and keep tracking Japan.

564
00:35:28,126 --> 00:35:30,837
I want the whole thing branded with
my Seal of Office, not the UN,

565
00:35:30,920 --> 00:35:32,797
have you got that?

566
00:35:35,216 --> 00:35:36,760
Anything I can do?

567
00:35:36,885 --> 00:35:39,512
I could make the tea?
Or isn't that American enough?

568
00:35:39,638 --> 00:35:42,599
I don't know, I could make grits.
What are grits anyway?

569
00:35:42,724 --> 00:35:44,643
If you could just sit.

570
00:35:46,603 --> 00:35:51,232
Misery guts.
What do you think? It's good, isn't it?

571
00:35:51,566 --> 00:35:53,151
It's beautiful.

572
00:35:54,319 --> 00:35:56,154
Some of my best work.

573
00:35:56,237 --> 00:36:01,242
Ministry of Defence,
I helped design this place.

574
00:36:05,038 --> 00:36:06,790
Every detail.

575
00:36:13,213 --> 00:36:17,175
-We've no time for sight-seeing!
-No, wait, shh, shh.

576
00:36:17,258 --> 00:36:19,094
-Can't you hear it?
-Hear what?

577
00:36:19,177 --> 00:36:22,222
-Doctor, my family's on board...
-Brilliant!

578
00:36:23,223 --> 00:36:24,599
This way!

579
00:36:37,987 --> 00:36:40,240
-Oh, at last!
-Oh, yes!

580
00:36:40,323 --> 00:36:42,742
What's it doing on the Valiant?

581
00:36:46,413 --> 00:36:48,331
-What the hell's he done?
-DOCTOR: Don't touch it!

582
00:36:48,456 --> 00:36:49,708
I'm not going to!

583
00:36:49,791 --> 00:36:53,545
MARTHA: What's he done, though?
Sounds like it's sick.

584
00:36:53,628 --> 00:36:55,630
DOCTOR: It can't be.

585
00:36:55,755 --> 00:36:58,633
No, no, no, no, no, no, it can't be.

586
00:36:58,717 --> 00:37:01,594
-Doctor, what is it?
-He's cannibalised the Tardis.

587
00:37:01,678 --> 00:37:04,139
Is this what I think it is?

588
00:37:04,222 --> 00:37:06,307
It's a paradox machine.

589
00:37:07,976 --> 00:37:09,894
Two minutes, everyone.

590
00:37:11,563 --> 00:37:13,940
According to the treaty,
all armed personnel

591
00:37:14,023 --> 00:37:17,235
are requested to leave the flight deck
immediately, thank you.

592
00:37:19,070 --> 00:37:20,280
Jelly baby?

593
00:37:20,363 --> 00:37:22,323
PRESIDENT: Broadcasting at 7:58,

594
00:37:22,407 --> 00:37:25,702
with the arrival timed for
0800 hours exactly.

595
00:37:25,827 --> 00:37:28,830
And good luck to all of us.

596
00:37:30,290 --> 00:37:32,834
As soon as this hits red, it activates.

597
00:37:32,959 --> 00:37:36,880
At this speed, it'll trigger at 8:02.

598
00:37:36,963 --> 00:37:39,549
First Contact is at 8:00,
then two minutes later...

599
00:37:39,674 --> 00:37:41,676
But what's it for?
What does a paradox machine do?

600
00:37:41,801 --> 00:37:45,180
-More important, can you stop it?
-Not till I know what it's doing.

601
00:37:45,305 --> 00:37:47,432
Touch the wrong bit,
blow up the solar system.

602
00:37:47,515 --> 00:37:49,267
Then we've gotta get to the Master!

603
00:37:49,350 --> 00:37:52,645
-Yeah, how we gonna stop him?
-Oh, I've got a way.

604
00:37:52,854 --> 00:37:55,023
Sorry, didn't I mention it?

605
00:37:56,274 --> 00:38:00,403
And in just 30 seconds' time,
we'll be going live to First Contact.

606
00:38:00,528 --> 00:38:02,489
It's been announced that Harold Saxon

607
00:38:02,572 --> 00:38:05,241
has invited President Winters
to take the address.

608
00:38:05,325 --> 00:38:08,703
It's 3:00 am in the morning
on the Eastern Seaboard

609
00:38:08,828 --> 00:38:13,541
and President Winters has been chosen
to lead the world into a new age.

610
00:38:15,752 --> 00:38:19,297
My fellow Americans, patriots,
people of the world.

611
00:38:19,380 --> 00:38:23,635
I stand before you today
as ambassador for humanity.

612
00:38:23,718 --> 00:38:26,971
A role I will undertake
with the utmost solemnity.

613
00:38:27,055 --> 00:38:30,266
Perhaps our Toclafane cousins
can offer us much.

614
00:38:30,391 --> 00:38:33,812
But what is important is not
that we gain material benefits,

615
00:38:33,895 --> 00:38:37,232
but that we learn to see ourselves anew.

616
00:38:37,357 --> 00:38:40,485
For as long as man
has looked to the stars

617
00:38:40,568 --> 00:38:43,488
he has wondered what
mysteries they hold.

618
00:38:43,613 --> 00:38:45,240
Now we know we are not alone.

619
00:38:45,365 --> 00:38:48,117
This plan, you gonna tell us?

620
00:38:48,243 --> 00:38:50,703
If I can get this around
the Master's neck,

621
00:38:50,787 --> 00:38:53,164
cancel out his perception,
they'll see him for real.

622
00:38:53,248 --> 00:38:57,752
It's just hard to go unnoticed
when everyone is on red alert.

623
00:38:58,086 --> 00:39:00,713
If they stop me, you've got a key.

624
00:39:00,839 --> 00:39:02,757
-Yes, sir.
-I'll get him.

625
00:39:03,466 --> 00:39:07,053
And I ask you now,
I ask of the human race,

626
00:39:07,136 --> 00:39:10,515
to join with me
in welcoming our friends.

627
00:39:10,598 --> 00:39:13,309
I give you the Toclafane.

628
00:39:21,609 --> 00:39:23,528
My name is Arthur Coleman Winters,

629
00:39:23,611 --> 00:39:25,864
President Elect of
the United States of America,

630
00:39:25,947 --> 00:39:29,075
and Designated Representative
of the United Nations.

631
00:39:29,158 --> 00:39:33,204
I welcome you to the planet Earth
and its associated moon.

632
00:39:33,288 --> 00:39:35,039
SPHERE 2: You're not the Master.

633
00:39:35,123 --> 00:39:37,083
SPHERE 1: We like the Mr Master.

634
00:39:37,166 --> 00:39:41,963
-SPHERE 3: We don't like you.
-I can be master if you so wish.

635
00:39:44,382 --> 00:39:47,886
I will accept mastery over you
if that is God's will.

636
00:39:47,969 --> 00:39:49,846
SPHERE 2: Man is stupid.

637
00:39:49,971 --> 00:39:51,890
SPHERE 3: Master is our friend.

638
00:39:51,973 --> 00:39:55,393
SPHERE 1:
Where's my Master, pretty please?

639
00:39:55,476 --> 00:39:58,146
Oh, all right, then. It's me!

640
00:39:58,396 --> 00:40:01,107
Ta-da! Sorry!

641
00:40:01,316 --> 00:40:03,776
Sorry, I have this effect,
people just get obsessed.

642
00:40:03,860 --> 00:40:08,865
Is it the smile, is it the aftershave,
is it the capacity to laugh at myself?

643
00:40:08,948 --> 00:40:10,783
I don't know! It's crazy!

644
00:40:10,909 --> 00:40:13,745
Saxon, what are you talking about?

645
00:40:13,828 --> 00:40:17,916
I'm taking control, Uncle Sam.
Starting with you.

646
00:40:19,292 --> 00:40:20,835
Kill him!

647
00:40:30,845 --> 00:40:34,515
Guards, nobody move! Nobody move!

648
00:40:34,641 --> 00:40:36,100
Now then!

649
00:40:36,184 --> 00:40:39,812
Peoples of the Earth,
please attend carefully.

650
00:40:39,896 --> 00:40:42,023
MASTER: Stop him!

651
00:40:43,566 --> 00:40:46,569
We meet at last, Doctor.

652
00:40:46,653 --> 00:40:48,780
Oh! I love saying that!

653
00:40:48,863 --> 00:40:50,365
Stop this! Stop it now!

654
00:40:50,448 --> 00:40:52,867
As if a perception filter is gonna
work on me.

655
00:40:52,951 --> 00:40:56,829
And look, it's the girlie and the freak.

656
00:40:56,913 --> 00:40:59,374
Although I'm not sure which one's which.

657
00:41:03,378 --> 00:41:05,964
Laser screwdriver. Who'd have sonic?

658
00:41:06,047 --> 00:41:09,467
And the good thing is, he's not dead
for long. I get to kill him again!

659
00:41:09,550 --> 00:41:11,135
Master, just calm down.

660
00:41:11,219 --> 00:41:13,262
Just look at what you're doing,
just stop.

661
00:41:13,346 --> 00:41:14,973
If you could see yourself.

662
00:41:15,765 --> 00:41:18,726
Do excuse me, little bit of personal
business. Back in a minute.

663
00:41:18,810 --> 00:41:20,395
Let him go.

664
00:41:21,479 --> 00:41:24,607
It's that sound, the sound in your head.
What if I can help?

665
00:41:24,691 --> 00:41:27,402
Oh! How to shut him up?

666
00:41:27,527 --> 00:41:29,696
I know! Memory lane!

667
00:41:31,531 --> 00:41:36,077
Professor Lazarus, remember him?
And his genetic manipulation device!

668
00:41:39,747 --> 00:41:42,834
What, did you think little Tish
got that job merely by coincidence?

669
00:41:42,917 --> 00:41:45,586
I've been laying traps for you
all this time!

670
00:41:45,670 --> 00:41:47,547
And if I can concentrate all that

671
00:41:47,630 --> 00:41:51,676
Lazarus technology into
one little screwdriver...

672
00:41:53,177 --> 00:41:58,099
But, ooh, if only I had
the Doctor's biological code.

673
00:41:58,599 --> 00:42:01,394
Oh! Wait a minute! I do!

674
00:42:02,311 --> 00:42:04,105
I've got his hand!

675
00:42:04,981 --> 00:42:10,153
And if Lazarus made himself younger,
what if I reverse it?

676
00:42:10,278 --> 00:42:12,989
Another 100 years?

677
00:42:19,328 --> 00:42:21,247
-Teleport.
-I can't.

678
00:42:22,040 --> 00:42:24,208
We can't stop him.

679
00:42:24,292 --> 00:42:25,960
Get out of here.

680
00:42:27,295 --> 00:42:28,629
Get out.

681
00:42:29,630 --> 00:42:31,466
(DOCTOR SCREAMING)

682
00:42:39,766 --> 00:42:42,602
Doctor, I've got you.

683
00:42:42,685 --> 00:42:45,229
MASTER: Ah, she's a would-be doctor.

684
00:42:45,646 --> 00:42:48,733
But tonight, Martha Jones,

685
00:42:48,816 --> 00:42:52,653
we've flown them in,
all the way from prison.

686
00:42:57,784 --> 00:43:00,119
-Mum.
-I'm sorry.

687
00:43:04,248 --> 00:43:07,919
The Toclafane. What are they?

688
00:43:09,796 --> 00:43:11,255
Who are they?

689
00:43:11,339 --> 00:43:16,594
Doctor, if I told you the truth,
your hearts would break.

690
00:43:17,428 --> 00:43:20,264
SPHERE 2: Is it time?
SPHERE 3: Is it ready?

691
00:43:20,348 --> 00:43:22,350
SPHERE 1: Is the machine singing?

692
00:43:24,852 --> 00:43:26,687
Two minutes past!

693
00:43:30,024 --> 00:43:33,444
So, Earthlings!

694
00:43:34,529 --> 00:43:37,615
Basically, um...

695
00:43:38,699 --> 00:43:40,409
End of the world.

696
00:43:41,577 --> 00:43:44,914
Here come the drums!

697
00:43:44,997 --> 00:43:47,875
(VOODOO CHILD PLAYING)

698
00:44:19,615 --> 00:44:23,578
-How many do you think?
-I don't know!

699
00:44:23,661 --> 00:44:25,746
MASTER: Six billion!

700
00:44:27,665 --> 00:44:29,417
Down you go, kids!

701
00:44:52,815 --> 00:44:54,817
Shall we decimate them?

702
00:44:55,943 --> 00:44:59,155
That sounds good, nice word, decimate.

703
00:45:01,532 --> 00:45:05,453
Remove one tenth of the population!

704
00:45:11,125 --> 00:45:13,711
WOMAN: This is Geneva!
We're getting slaughtered down here!

705
00:45:13,794 --> 00:45:16,714
Valiant, report! Help us!
For God"s sake help us!

706
00:45:18,966 --> 00:45:22,220
MAN: This is London, Valiant.
This is London. What do we do?

707
00:45:22,303 --> 00:45:26,766
They're killing us! The Toclafane...
They're killing us!

708
00:46:09,767 --> 00:46:12,270
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

709
00:46:17,149 --> 00:46:18,818
I'm coming back.

710
00:46:21,362 --> 00:46:23,864
And so it came to pass

711
00:46:24,031 --> 00:46:28,911
that the human race fell
and the Earth was no more.

712
00:46:30,246 --> 00:46:35,876
And I looked down upon my new dominion
as master of all.

713
00:46:37,003 --> 00:46:40,589
And I thought it good.

714
00:46:43,509 --> 00:46:45,594
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

715
00:47:42,443 --> 00:47:44,153
MASTER: Ever since I was a child,

716
00:47:44,236 --> 00:47:47,490
I looked into the Vortex,
that's when it chose me.

717
00:47:47,573 --> 00:47:50,451
The drumming, the call to war.

718
00:48:03,839 --> 00:48:05,549
(DOCTOR SCREAMING)

719
00:48:05,633 --> 00:48:07,718
MASTER: Can't you hear it?

